Command : 
kubectl scale deploy backend --replicas=2
Can be written as following 
kubectl scale  deployment/backend --replicas=2

*Note*
This change is applied imperatively. On the next kubectl apply of the original YAML file,
the backend will revert to 1 replica, as defined in the manifest.


The change can be seen immediately:
kubectl get pods

NAME                        READY   STATUS    RESTARTS   AGE
backend-576ccdb8d-94nzp     1/1     Running   0          5m7s
backend-576ccdb8d-hbqbz     1/1     Running   0          3m14s
frontend-7b9bcbbfc4-95n86   1/1     Running   0          5m7s
